########################
# History of the AVsub #
########################

AVsub 2.2.4 [2021.10.03]
------------------------
- F2240: Fixed the error where the required temporary folders could not be created when option "-o/--output" is not used.
- N2240: Now it is checked whether the current version is a yanked version.
- Code improvements.


AVsub 2.2.3 [2021.10.01] (yanked)
---------------------------------
- C2230: Option "-o/--output" now requires a folder where the basename does not contain spaces.
- C2231: Option "-o/--output" now requires an existing folder to operate.
- Code improvements.
- Performance improvements.
- Quality improvements.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- User interface has been improved.
- Type annotations have been improved.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 2.2.2 [2021.09.22]
------------------------
- F2220: Fixed the "FileExistsError" that could occur when providing an existing file for the "-o/--output" option.
- F2221: Fixed the error where the "repeater" feature could not print the last error message.
- Code improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- User interface has been improved.
- PEP 8 compliance.


AVsub 2.2.1 [2021.09.08]
------------------------
- F2210: Fixed another "OSError: [WinError 123]" that could occur due to incorrectly entered or non-existent pathname.
- F2211: Fixed the error of printing the output folder even there is no such folder.
- Code improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- Documentation has been improved.
- Typo fixes.


AVsub 2.2.0 [2021.08.27]
------------------------
- F2200: Fixed the "OSError: [WinError 123]" that could occur due to incorrectly entered pathname.
- F2201: Fixed the error where the '0' value could not be used for the '--size' option.
- N2200: Added a command-line option that allows users to continue processing when fatal FFmpeg errors are encountered.
- N2201: Users can now provide a trim value in HH:MM:SS syntax.
- N2202: A new 'data' value is now available for the '--remove' option.
- N2203: It is now checked whether the current operating system is supported or not.
- N2204: Added a new cleaner for folders.
- C2200: Operation results are now displayed in reverse order for the log file.
- C2201: FFmpeg check feature has been improved.
- C2202: Privileged access is now prohibited by default.
- C2203: When a fatal FFmpeg error is encountered, incomplete items no longer appear as "not completed".
- Code improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- User interface has been improved.
- Type annotations have been improved.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 2.1.0 [2021.08.18]
------------------------
- N2100: Added a command-line option that allows users to change the output folder location.
- N2101: Added a command-line option that logs operation results to a file.
- N2102: Now FFmpeg is tested before the process starts.
- C2010: The default value for the 'no-open-dir' option has been changed from "empty" to "always" (POSIX only).
- C2011: Non-English letters are no longer valid for the input file extension.
- Code improvements.
- Performance improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 2.0.0 [2021.08.12]
------------------------
- P2000: Removed Python version 3.5 support.
- F2000: Fixed an error that caused action to be taken for files that would not be processed.
- F2001: Fixed the error that caused unprocessed items to appear as "not completed" after telling the program to stop.
- F2002: Fixed the error of continuing to print output after telling the program to stop.
- N2000: If the input file is hidden, the output file is now also marked as hidden.
- N2001: A new 'veryslow' value is now available for the 'speed' option.
- C2000: A constant encoding speed value is now used when no value is specified for the 'speed' option.
- C2001: Users can now decide in more detail when not to open the output folder.
- C2002: A constant value is now used when no value is specified for the 'no-open-dir' option.
- C2003: Removed default values for the following options: 'box', 'color1', 'color2', 'font', 'position', 'size'.
- C2004: The '-' and '_' characters and some non-English letters are now valid for the input file extension.
- C2005: Temporary folder now also opens in GNU/Linux operating system (again).
- C2006: Now all error messages are shown when contradictory option check fails.
- Code improvements.
- Performance improvements.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 1.4.0 [2021.07.29]
------------------------
- N1400: Added a command-line option that allows users to disable opening the output folder at the end.
- Code improvements.
- Performance improvements.
- Exit statuses have been changed; 0: All is well, 2: Error, 3: Fatal.
- User interface has been improved.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 1.3.0 [2021.07.22]
------------------------
- N1300: Added a command-line option that allows users to provide a custom FFmpeg argument list.
- N1301: Added a command-line option that can disable choosing all streams.
- C1300: If specified, the FFmpeg command is now also shown for hardsub manual operations as well.
- C1301: The default value for the log verbosity level has been changed from "warning" to "error".
- C1302: Log verbosity level can be increased even more.
- Code improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- PEP 8 compliance.


AVsub 1.2.1 [2021.07.05]
------------------------
- F1210: Fixed an error when terminating the program with SIGTSTP on GNU/Linux (it reset to the original behavior).
- Code improvements.
- Performance improvements.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.2.0 [2021.06.19]
------------------------
- F1200: Fixed the error "RuntimeError: reentrant call inside" when terminating the program with an exit signal.
- F1201: Fixed some errors that caused the program to crash when "PermissionError" occurred.
- F1202: Fixed the error where the '0' value could not be used for the 'compress' option.
- F1203: Fixed an error that caused some inputs that did not represent the current folder to be treated as the current folder.
- N1200: Added a command-line option that can trim the input.
- N1201: Added a command-line option that allows excluding files with certain extension(s).
- N1202: Added a command-line option that allows selecting files with certain extension(s) only.
- N1203: Added an option that allows users to skip checking some command-line arguments.
- C1200: The input file extension is now preserved if the output extension is equal to '-'.
- C1201: The ability to check for updates for AVsub has been improved.
- C1202: A constant compression value is now used when no value is specified for the 'compress' option.
- C1203: The value that can be entered for the 'compress' option is now limited to the range 0-51.
- Code improvements.
- Added some extra error handling.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.
- Documentation has been improved.


AVsub 1.1.1 [2021.05.12]
------------------------
- F1110: Fixed an error that could cause the temporary subtitle file not to be deleted when exiting.
- C1110: If specified, the FFmpeg command is now also shown for automatic operations as well.
- Code improvements.


AVsub 1.1.0 [2021.05.03]
------------------------
- F1100: Fixed the error "TypeError: startfile() takes no keyword arguments" in Python 3.5.
- N1100: Added a command-line option that can change audio channels.
- N1101: Added a command-line option that shows the FFmpeg command during processing.
- N1102: It is now checked if there is a new version for AVsub when no arguments are specified.
- C1100: Root folders are no longer considered hidden in Linux.
- C1101: Fatal FFmpeg error is now also displayed at the end of output for convenience.
- Code improvements.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.2 [2021.04.12]
------------------------
- F1020: Fixed an "AttributeError" that could occur on exiting.
- C1020: Unprocessed items in a folder can now be determined as "not processed" after an exit request.
- C1021: The default value for the subtitle font size has been changed from 18 to 20.
- C1022: All other temporary folders are now collected under one main temporary folder.
- C1023: Temporary folder now opens only in Windows operating system.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.1 [2021.03.16]
------------------------
- Code improvements.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.0 [2021.03.10]
------------------------
- First version.
